  "description": "Two small, dark geese with small heads and bills. Black head, bill, breast, primaries, and tail. White undertail coverts. White, incomplete necklace around middle of black neck. Never got a great look at the belly but from what I could see it appeared dark, consistent with \"Black\" Brant. Age determined by mantle feathers with whitish distal margins, side of body blotchy. Upperwing-coverts with whitish ends. Secondaries and inner primaries tipped with white.Behaviors: Swimming with Canada GeeseCall: not heardPlumage: juvenile",
